main event: A UFO sighting was reported on 11 February 1956 in Bremerton, Washington, involving a round object estimated to be three feet across and traveling at an estimated speed of 600 mph.
interesting points: The object emitted a light blue streak during its movement,The sighting lasted approximately ten seconds,The sighting involved a ground-visual observation type,The observer believed the object was possibly an aircraft due to its straight line course,The report is part of Project Blue Book, the U.S. Air Force's systematic study of UFOs.
witness description: The observer provided a visual account of the sighting.
